            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29504",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm not seeing what the problem is here. We could catch the Db_Exception and throw a Log_Exception, but this looks like yucky exception chaining; I don't see any benefit. Could you please elaborate on the scenario in which you'd get an infinite loop?\n\n,Wil",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-16T14:09:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-16T14:09:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29508",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Well there is none. Anyway ErrorHandler throws the exception out of the Frontcontroller, so such a code is not a problem :\n{code}\ntry {\n   $obj->something(), \/\/ a DB exception is thrown here\n} catch { Zend_Exception $e) { \/\/ but I want a wide catch\n   $log->log($e); \/\/ $log has a db backend, it will throw an exception\n}\n{code}\n\nSuch a use case can happen in an MVC app where ErrorHandler widely catch exceptions to log them.\nAnyway, a try catch should be done on the log operation as well, all right for me\n\n-Closing-",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
